label.value: decreased protein localization to cell tip, with protein distributed in plasma membrane or cortex

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell tip is decreased, and an increased amount of the protein is instead detected distributed throughout the plasma membrane and/or cell cortex.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to cell tip, with protein mislocalized to cytoplasm

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell tip is abolished, and the protein is present in the cytoplasm instead.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: mislocalized, misoriented septum

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell has a septum that is in an abnormal location and is not perpendicular to the long axis of the cell. The normal location is at the midpoint of the long axis of the cell.

definition.value: Note that the location of the septum is determined by the location of the contractile ring, which in turn is determined by the location of the cell division site, so an abnormality in cell division site determination can be inferred from this phenotype. Consider also annotating to 'mislocalized actomyosin contractile ring' (FYPO:0001369) because if the contractile ring forms in an abnormal location, the septum will also do so.

label.value: abnormal secondary cell septum biogenesis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which secondary cell septum biogenesis is abnormal. Secondary cell septum biogenesis results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of the secondary cell septum during cytokinesis.

definition.value: Consider also annotating to 'abnormal contractile ring localization' (FYPO:0000033) because if the contractile ring forms in an abnormal location, the septum will also do so. The positions of both the contractile ring and the septum are determined by the processes that select the site of cell division.

label.value: kinked septum

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell forms a septum that is kinked, i.e. has multiple angles along its length.

label.value: explosive cytokinetic cell separation resulting in vegetative cell lysis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cell separation is instantaneous and asymmetrical, with a ripped primary septum. Explosive cell separation takes a few seconds (rather than 5-6 minutes as in wild type) and involves asymmetrical degradation and/or breakage of the septum edging followed by an abrupt tear of a weak primary septum and an instantaneous curvature of the secondary septum.

label.value: normal protein phosphorylation during cellular response to glucose starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to glucose starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term. Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: normal protein-protein interaction during cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of one protein to another is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide. The relevant proteins may include the one encoded by the mutated gene, or may both be encoded by different genes.

definition.value: This term can be used for any protein-protein interaction that is tested in a mutant, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased chromatin silencing at rDNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing at ribosomal DNA repeat regions is decreased.

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).

label.value: decreased chromatin silencing at centromere central core

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the chromatin silencing at the central core of the centromeric regions is decreased.

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes at the centromere central core may reflect the assembly or maintenance of CENP-A-containing chromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'CENP-A containing chromatin' (GO:0061638), and the biological process term 'CENP-A containing chromatin organization' (GO:0061641).

label.value: abolished tRNA wobble base 5-methoxycarbonylmethyl-2-thiouridine biosynthesis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the modification of a wobble base uridine residue in a tRNA to 5-methoxycarbonylmethyl-2-thiouridine is abolished.

label.value: normal histone acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone acetylation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: sensitive to zearalenone

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to zearalenone. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of zearalenone that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H3-K14 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 14 of histone H3 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal rate of microtubule polymerization during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of microtubule polymerization, i.e. the addition of tubulin dimers to a microtubule, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: delayed onset of protein localization to mitotic spindle

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle begins later than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: interphase microtubules present during mitosis

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the long cytoplasmic microtubules characteristic of interphase cells remain present after mitosis begins and the mitotic spindle forms.

label.value: abolished protein oxidation during cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the oxidation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, does not occur during a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal hydrogen peroxide catabolism

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the chemical breakdown of hydrogen peroxide is abnormal.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 methylation at heterochromatin island during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at heterochromatin islands occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 methylation at heterochromatin domain during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at heterochromatin domains occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 methylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 methylation at heterochromatin island during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at heterochromatin islands is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 methylation at heterochromatin domain during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at heterochromatin domains is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 methylation at centromere outer repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at centromere outer repeat regions is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased transposable element-derived small RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of small RNA (such as siRNA) derived from transposable element transcripts measured in a cell is lower than normal.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased RNA splicing at cryptic splice sites

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of splicing of RNA primary transcripts at sites that are not normally frequently used (or not spliced at all) is increased.

label.value: decreased anaerobic cell population growth

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cell growth is decreased relative to normal under anaerobic conditions.

label.value: abnormal phosphodiesterase I activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of phosphodiesterase I activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased phosphodiesterase I activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of phosphodiesterase I activity is decreased.

label.value: unequal mitotic sister chromatid segregation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mitotic sister chromatid segregation fails to separate chromosomes into two equal masses. Unequal mitotic sister chromatid separation may be complete, with two distinct unequal DNA masses located at or near the ends of an elongated mitotic spindle, or incomplete.

definition.value: Consider also annotating to 'abnormal sister chromatid biorientation' (FYPO:0000326) because a problem with biorientation usually results in unequal chromosome segregation.

label.value: decreased splicing of mRNA introns with low A/U content

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of mRNA splicing via the spliceosome is decreased, where introns have low A/U content.

label.value: decreased splicing of long introns

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth the occurrence of splicing of introns longer than about 45 nucleotides is decreased.

label.value: decreased mRNA splicing, via spliceosome, intron-specific

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mRNA splicing via the spliceosome takes place normally for some, but is decreased for other, specific introns.

label.value: telophase nuclear clustering

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the daughter nuclei formed by mitosis cluster in the middle of the cell during telophase. Normally, daughter nuclei move away from the cell division site during mitotic telophase.

definition.value: This phenotype may be observed when cytokinesis fails.

label.value: normal mitotic S phase progression

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through S phase of the mitotic cell cycle is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abolished histone H3 binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of histone H3 binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

definition.value: This term can be used for any protein-protein interaction that is affected by a mutation, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased level of histone H3 at centromere inner repeat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of histone H3 measured at centromere inner repeat regions is higher than normal.

label.value: decreased level of histone H3 at dh repeat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of histone H3 measured at centromeric dh repeat regions is lower than normal.

label.value: premature septum assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which septum assembly begins earlier than normal, e.g. before metaphase is complete.

label.value: decreased transcription from SRE promoter

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription from a promoter that contains one or more sterol regulatory elements (SREs) occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: abolished cell population growth on proline nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which a cell population does not grow in a medium containing L-proline as the nitrogen source.

definition.value: Use this term for a population of cells that does not grow with proline as the nitrogen source, but does grow using a different nitrogen source (a cell population that does not grow on any media would be considered inviable). Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: abolished amino acid import during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of one or more amino acids into the cell is abolished.

label.value: abolished arginine import

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of arginine into the cell is abolished.

label.value: abolished proline import

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of proline into the cell is abolished.

label.value: abnormal proline import

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of proline into the cell is abnormal.

label.value: decreased proline import

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of proline into the cell occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: increased proline import

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of proline into the cell occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: normal proline import

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of proline into the cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
